# Portfolio Website Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Create a modern, premium portfolio website for a software developer, inspired by [Brittany Chiang's portfolio](https://brittanychiang.com/). The design will focus on a dark aesthetic, clean typography, single-page seamless scrolling, and subtle interactive elements (spotlight cursor, hover states).

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> - I will create the project in a new folder `portfolio` within your current workspace.
> - The design will be implemented using **Vanilla CSS** to match the premium custom feel of the reference.
> - Content will be placeholders as requested ("content i'll make the changes").

## Proposed Changes
We will create a new React application using Vite in the `portfolio` directory.

### Architecture
- **Framework**: React (Vite)
- **Styling**: Vanilla CSS (CSS Variables for theming)
- **Icons**: `react-icons` (if needed) or SVGs.

### File Structure
- `src/styles/`: Global variables, reset, fonts.
- `src/components/`: Reusable UI components.
    - `Layout.jsx`: Main wrapper handling the grid layout (Sidebar + Content).
    - `Sidebar.jsx`: Fixed container for profile info and nav.
    - `MainContent.jsx`: Scrollable container for sections.
    - `Nav.jsx`: Navigation links.
    - `Experience.jsx`, `Projects.jsx`, `About.jsx`: Content sections.
- `src/App.jsx`: Entry point.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- `npm run build` to verify build success.

### Manual Verification
- Visual check of the dark theme and layout.
- Verify smooth scrolling and active state updating in navigation.
- Verify the "spotlight" hover effect using the browser tool or visual inspection.
